Navigating filesystems and managing directories:   
   
   
7.cd                                                   it is used to change the current working directory.                                       cd
8.rmdir                                              it is used to remove files and directories.                                             rm file.txt
9.mkdir                                             it  is used to create new directories (folders).                                     mkdir(name of folder)
10.pwd                                                it is used to confirm current directory                                               pwd  

Navigating filesystem and managing files and access permissions:

11.cp                                                              which is used to copy files in a                             
                                                                    current working progress .
                                                                    Here It seems like you want to copy                                   cp file 1 file 2
                                                                    a file named "file 1" to another file 
                                                                    named "file2".

12.rm                                                           it is used to remove files and directories.                            rm file.txt

13.mv                                                           it  is used to move or rename files and directories.                       mv       olddirectory                                                                                                                               newdirectory

